hdlcEntry.name: hdlcEntry
hdlcEntry.description: Defines the contents of each line in the RAD HDLC Table.

hdlcProtocol.name: hdlcProtocol
hdlcProtocol.description: The HDLC protocol type V35 - HDLC encapsulated over V35 X21 - HDLC encapsulated over X21 RS530 - HDLC encapsulated over RS530

hdlcRateResolution.name: hdlcRateResolution
hdlcRateResolution.description: The baud rate of the internal clock.

hdlcTxClockSource.name: hdlcTxClockSource
hdlcTxClockSource.description: The baud rate of the internal clock.

hdlcLoopbackState.name: hdlcLoopbackState
hdlcLoopbackState.description: internal - All data coming from the network port is looped back external - All data comming from the line is looped back.

hdlcTxClockPolarity.name: hdlcTxClockPolarity
hdlcTxClockPolarity.description: normal - The transmitted data is sampled at the middle of bit time inverse - The transmitted data is sampled at the end of the bit time (high data rate/long cable).

hdlcFlowControl.name: hdlcFlowControl
hdlcFlowControl.description: Enable/Disable the CTS/RTS flow control signals.

hdlcLineRate.name: hdlcLineRate
hdlcLineRate.description: The rate values for HDLC are n*56/64Kbps, where 1<=n<=32, 64, 128 and the following values: 1544, 3088, 6176. The rate values for HSSI is nMbps, where 1<=n<=52.

hdlcLOF.name: hdlcLOF
hdlcLOF.description: Total number of seconds the port is in Loss Of Frame state.

hdlcRxClockPolarity.name: hdlcRxClockPolarity
hdlcRxClockPolarity.description: normal - The received data is sampled at the middle of bit time inverse - The received data is sampled at the end of the bit time (high data rate/long cable).

hdlcCurrentEntry.name: hdlcCurrentEntry
hdlcCurrentEntry.description: An entry in the HDLC Current table.

hdlcCurrentIfIndex.name: hdlcCurrentIfIndex
hdlcCurrentIfIndex.description: The index of the HDLC interface. It may be ifIndex.

hdlcCurrentStatus.name: hdlcCurrentStatus
hdlcCurrentStatus.description: The statuses of the current interval: 0 - Valid. 1 - redundantLinkSwitch - the link has been switched by a redundancy mechanism. 2 - discontinuity - module was partialy out. 4 - notValid - module is out.

hdlcCurrentLOF.name: hdlcCurrentLOF
hdlcCurrentLOF.description: The counter associated with the number of seconds the port is in Loss Of Frame state, encountered by the HDLC interface in the current 15 minute interval.

hdlcCurrentInFrames.name: hdlcCurrentInFrames
hdlcCurrentInFrames.description: The counter associated with the number of received frames, encountered by the HDLC interface in the current 15 minute interval.

hdlcCurrentInErrors.name: hdlcCurrentInErrors
hdlcCurrentInErrors.description: The counter associated with the number of Errored received frames, encountered by the HDLC interface in the current 15 minute interval.

hdlcCurrentOutFrames.name: hdlcCurrentOutFrames
hdlcCurrentOutFrames.description: The counter associated with the number of transmitted frames, encountered by the HDLC interface in the current 15 minute interval.

hdlcCurrentAbortedFrames.name: hdlcCurrentAbortedFrames
hdlcCurrentAbortedFrames.description: The counter associated with the number of frames, in which at least seven consecutive '1'-s (Abort sequence) were encountered by the HDLC interface in the current 15 minute interval.

hdlcCurrentLengthError.name: hdlcCurrentLengthError
hdlcCurrentLengthError.description: The counter associated with the number of received frames with length error, encountered by the HDLC interface in the current 15 minute interval.

hdlcIntervalEntry.name: hdlcIntervalEntry
hdlcIntervalEntry.description: An entry in the HDLC Interval table.

hdlcIntervalIfIndex.name: hdlcIntervalIfIndex
hdlcIntervalIfIndex.description: The index of the HDLC interface. It may be ifIndex.

hdlcIntervalNumber.name: hdlcIntervalNumber
hdlcIntervalNumber.description: A number between 1 and 96, where 1 is the most recently completed 15 minute interval and 96 is the least recently completed 15 minutes interval (assuming that all 96 intervals exist).

hdlcIntervalStatus.name: hdlcIntervalStatus
hdlcIntervalStatus.description: The statuses of the current interval: 0 - Valid. 1 - redundantLinkSwitch - the link has been switched by a redundancy mechanism. 2 - discontinuity - module was partialy out. 4 - notValid - module is out.

hdlcIntervalLOF.name: hdlcIntervalLOF
hdlcIntervalLOF.description: The counter associated with the number of seconds the port is in Loss Of Frame state, encountered by an HDLC interface in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals.

hdlcIntervalInFrames.name: hdlcIntervalInFrames
hdlcIntervalInFrames.description: The counter associated with the number of received frames, encountered by the HDLC interface in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals.

hdlcIntervalInErrors.name: hdlcIntervalInErrors
hdlcIntervalInErrors.description: The counter associated with the number of Errored received frames, encountered by the HDLC interface in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals.

hdlcIntervalOutFrames.name: hdlcIntervalOutFrames
hdlcIntervalOutFrames.description: The counter associated with the number of transmitted frames, encountered by the HDLC interface in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals.

hdlcIntervalAbortedFrames.name: hdlcIntervalAbortedFrames
hdlcIntervalAbortedFrames.description: The counter associated with the number of frames, in which at least seven consecutive '1'-s (Abort sequence) were encountered by the HDLC interface in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals.

hdlcIntervalLengthError.name: hdlcIntervalLengthError
hdlcIntervalLengthError.description: The counter associated with the number of received frames with length error, encountered by the HDLC interface in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals.

smUNIVersion.name: smUNIVersion
smUNIVersion.description: The UNI version that is used by both sides.

smPolicing.name: smPolicing
smPolicing.description: The type of the police action performed on the cells transmitted from the user side to the network side.

smOpenedSesssions.name: smOpenedSesssions
smOpenedSesssions.description: The number of SVC sessions currently opened.

smUserRejectedSessions.name: smUserRejectedSessions
smUserRejectedSessions.description: The number of sessions that the user side rejected to open.

smNetworkRejectedSessions.name: smNetworkRejectedSessions
smNetworkRejectedSessions.description: The number of sessions that the Network side rejected.

smHostRejectedSessions.name: smHostRejectedSessions
smHostRejectedSessions.description: The number of sessions that the device rejected to open.

smVclILMISessionVpi.name: smVclILMISessionVpi
smVclILMISessionVpi.description: ILMI Keep alive session VPI channel. Default: 0. (VCI=16, fixed).

rtrConfigIfEntry.name: rtrConfigIfEntry
rtrConfigIfEntry.description: Each entry defines a configured interface.

rtrConfigIfIndex.name: rtrConfigIfIndex
rtrConfigIfIndex.description: This variable uniquely identifies the interface. It is used as a cross reference in other system tables

rtrConfigIfType.name: rtrConfigIfType
rtrConfigIfType.description: This variable identifies the type of the specific entry in the rtrDynamicIfConfigTable. This field is writable only at creation time (i.e., when value of status is underCreation).

rtrConfigIfName.name: rtrConfigIfName
rtrConfigIfName.description: This variable provides a logical name to a specific entry in rtrConfigIfTable. It is also used in identifying the Driver interfaces.

rtrConfigIfStatus.name: rtrConfigIfStatus
rtrConfigIfStatus.description: The status of the ConfigEntry. The choices are those defined in SNMPv2-TC. Only: active, createAndWait, and destroy will be used. active - The conceptual row is available for use by the managed device. createAndWait - A new instance of a conceptual row is desired, but not to have it available for use by the managed device. destroy - Delete all instances associated with an existing conceptual row.

rtrIfCfgEntry.name: rtrIfCfgEntry
rtrIfCfgEntry.description: An entry in the Router Interface Configuration Table.

rtrIfCfgIndex.name: rtrIfCfgIndex
rtrIfCfgIndex.description: This object indicates the Router Interface Index. (In some cases it will be equal to the Router Interface ifIndex).

rtrIfCfgIpAddress.name: rtrIfCfgIpAddress
rtrIfCfgIpAddress.description: IP Address of the Router Interface.

rtrIfCfgRowStatus.name: rtrIfCfgRowStatus
rtrIfCfgRowStatus.description: This object enables the user to create/delete entries of this table.

rtrIfCfgIfIndex.name: rtrIfCfgIfIndex
rtrIfCfgIfIndex.description: ifIndex of the device interface connected to this Router Interface.

rtrIfCfgType.name: rtrIfCfgType
rtrIfCfgType.description: The Router Interface Type. atm - ATM router interface lis - Logical IP Subnet router interface. ethernet - Ethernet router interface.

rtrIfCfgVlanId.name: rtrIfCfgVlanId
rtrIfCfgVlanId.description: The VLAN ID assigned to Tagged frames transmitted from this Router Interface. The value inserted should be a defined VLAN.

rtrIfCfgMtu.name: rtrIfCfgMtu
rtrIfCfgMtu.description: The size of the largest packet which can be sent/received on the interface, specified in octets. For interfaces that are used for transmitting network datagrams, this is the size of the largest network datagram that can be sent on the interface.

rtrIpAddrTable.name: rtrIpAddrTable
rtrIpAddrTable.description: This table is parralel to MIB II IpAddrTable, and is used to add/delete entries to/from that table. In addition it contains private objects.

rtrIpAddrEntry.name: rtrIpAddrEntry
rtrIpAddrEntry.description: The addressing information for one of this entity's IP addresses.

rtrIpAdEntAddr.name: rtrIpAdEntAddr
rtrIpAdEntAddr.description: The IP address to which this entry's addressing information pertains.

rtrIpAdEntIfIndex.name: rtrIpAdEntIfIndex
rtrIpAdEntIfIndex.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the interface to which this entry is applicable. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex.

rtrIpAdEntNetMask.name: rtrIpAdEntNetMask
rtrIpAdEntNetMask.description: The subnet mask associated with the IP address of this entry. The value of the mask is an IP address with all the network bits set to 1 and all the hosts bits set to 0.

rtrIpAdEntForwardIpBroadcast.name: rtrIpAdEntForwardIpBroadcast
rtrIpAdEntForwardIpBroadcast.description: This variable controls forwarding of IP (sub)net-directed broadcasts destined for an attached sub(net).

rtrIpAdEntStatus.name: rtrIpAdEntStatus
rtrIpAdEntStatus.description: The Status variable is used to create and destroy a Ip Addresses.

rtrIcmpGenErrMsgEnable.name: rtrIcmpGenErrMsgEnable
rtrIcmpGenErrMsgEnable.description: This variable controlls the ability to generate ICMP error messages

rtrIcmpRdTable.name: rtrIcmpRdTable
rtrIcmpRdTable.description: This table contains ICMP Router Discovery parameters configurated per IP interface.

rtrIcmpRdEntry.name: rtrIcmpRdEntry
rtrIcmpRdEntry.description: The ICMP parameters configurated for IP interface.

rtrIcmpRdIpAddr.name: rtrIcmpRdIpAddr
rtrIcmpRdIpAddr.description: The IP address to which this entry's information pertains.

rtrIcmpRdIpAdvertAddr.name: rtrIcmpRdIpAdvertAddr
rtrIcmpRdIpAdvertAddr.description: The IP destination address to be used for multicast Router Advertisements sent from the interface. The only permissible values are the all-systems multicast address, 224.0.0.1, or the limited-broadcast address, 255.255.255.255.

rtrIcmpRdMaxAdvertInterval.name: rtrIcmpRdMaxAdvertInterval
rtrIcmpRdMaxAdvertInterval.description: The maximum time allowed between sending multicast Router Advertisements from the interface, in seconds. Must be no less than 4 seconds and no greater than 1800 seconds.

rtrIcmpRdMinAdvertInterval.name: rtrIcmpRdMinAdvertInterval
rtrIcmpRdMinAdvertInterval.description: The minimum time allowed between sending unsolicited multicast Router Advertisements from the interface, in seconds. Must be no less than 3 seconds and no greater than rtrIcmpRdMaxAdvertInterval. Default: 0.75 * rtrIcmpRdMaxAdvertInterval.

rtrIcmpRdAdvertLifetime.name: rtrIcmpRdAdvertLifetime
rtrIcmpRdAdvertLifetime.description: The maximum length of time that the advertised addresses are to be considered as valid. Must be no less than rtrIcmpRdMaxAdvertInterval and no greater than 9000 seconds. Default: 3 * rtrIcmpRdMaxAdvertInterval.

rtrIcmpRdAdvertise.name: rtrIcmpRdAdvertise
rtrIcmpRdAdvertise.description: A flag indicating whether or not the address is to be advertised.

rtrIcmpRdPreferenceLevel.name: rtrIcmpRdPreferenceLevel
rtrIcmpRdPreferenceLevel.description: The preferability of the address as a default router address, relative to other router addresses on the same subnet.

rtrIcmpRdEntStatus.name: rtrIcmpRdEntStatus
rtrIcmpRdEntStatus.description: Setting of any value to this object set values of all fields to the default values.

rtrRip2IfConfTable.name: rtrRip2IfConfTable
rtrRip2IfConfTable.description: This table is an extension of rip2IfConfTable (RFC 1724 ,RIP 2). It means that every time somebody creates/destroys a row in the rip2IfConfTable, the same row should be automatically created/destroyed in this table.

rtrRip2IfConfAddress.name: rtrRip2IfConfAddress
rtrRip2IfConfAddress.description: The IP Address of this system on the indicated subnet. For unnumbered interfaces, the value 0.0.0.N, where the least significant 24 bits (N) is the ifIndex for the IP Interface in network byte order

rtrRip2IfConfVirtualDis.name: rtrRip2IfConfVirtualDis
rtrRip2IfConfVirtualDis.description: This variable defines the virtual number of hops assigned to the interface specified by rtrIfIpAddrIndex. This enables fine-tuning of the RIP routing algorithm.

rtrRip2IfConfAutoSend.name: rtrRip2IfConfAutoSend
rtrRip2IfConfAutoSend.description: When set to enable only the default route is sent through the interface. When set to disable, regular RIPs are sent.

rtrRip2IfConfRipEnable.name: rtrRip2IfConfRipEnable
rtrRip2IfConfRipEnable.description: This object shows whether RIP Protocol is enabled on the current interface.

rtrArpDeleteTable.name: rtrArpDeleteTable
rtrArpDeleteTable.description: Setting this object to any not-null value has the effect of deleting all entries of the ARP table.

rtrArpInactiveTimeOut.name: rtrArpInactiveTimeOut
rtrArpInactiveTimeOut.description: This variable defines the maximum time period (in second) that can pass between ARP requests concerning an entry in the ARP table. After this time period, the entry is deleted from the table.

rtrArpProxy.name: rtrArpProxy
rtrArpProxy.description: When ARP Proxy is enabled, the router can respond to ARP requests for nodes located on a different sub-net, provided they are it its network table. The router responds with its own MAC address. When ARP Proxy is disabled, the router responds only to ARP requests for its own IP addresses.

rtrNatIfConfTable.name: rtrNatIfConfTable
rtrNatIfConfTable.description: A list of interfaces which require separate NAT configuration.

rtrNatIfConfEntry.name: rtrNatIfConfEntry
rtrNatIfConfEntry.description: A single routing domain in a single subnet.

rtrNatIfVirtualAddress.name: rtrNatIfVirtualAddress
rtrNatIfVirtualAddress.description: The IP Address of the virtual subnet to be translated by the 'NAT box' attached to this interface.

rtrNatIfVirtualMask.name: rtrNatIfVirtualMask
rtrNatIfVirtualMask.description: The subnet Mask of the virtual subnet.

rtrNatIfConfStatus.name: rtrNatIfConfStatus
rtrNatIfConfStatus.description: Writing 'destroy' has the effect of deleting this interface.

rtrNatIfRealAddress.name: rtrNatIfRealAddress
rtrNatIfRealAddress.description: The IP Address of the real subnet which is used by 'NAT box' for translation.

rtrNatIfRealMask.name: rtrNatIfRealMask
rtrNatIfRealMask.description: The subnet Mask of the real subnet.

rtrNatIfType.name: rtrNatIfType
rtrNatIfType.description: NAT type. static - Translate a specific virtual IP network to a specific real IP network. TCP, UDP and ICMP sessions originated both in real and virtual networks will be translated. dynamic - (Concurrent) Translate real IP network to larger or equal virtual IP network. TCP, UDP and ICMP sessions originated in virtual networks only can be translated and sessions originated in real networks will be rejected. A session that starts in the NAT system will be active until there will be no traffic for aging timeout period. pat - (Port Address Translation/ Single IP). Translate one real IP address to virtual IP network. TCP, UDP and ICMP sessions originated in virtual network only can be translated, sessions originated in real network will be rejected. A session that starts in the NAT system will be active until there will be no traffic for aging timeout period. transparent - In transparent mode all frames belonging to the defined IP network will be forwarded with no translation: virtual = real.

rtrPatTable.name: rtrPatTable
rtrPatTable.description: Port Address Translation (PAT - single IP NAT) configuration Table.

rtrPatEntry.name: rtrPatEntry
rtrPatEntry.description: Each entry describe unique mapping between real IP address, range of ports and protocol, to local (virtual) IP address. Ports are used in the TCP (rfc793) to name the ends of logical connections which carry long term conversations. For the purpose of providing services to unknown callers, a service contact port is defined.

rtrPatRealAddress.name: rtrPatRealAddress
rtrPatRealAddress.description: The real IP Address used for translation

rtrPatVirtualAddress.name: rtrPatVirtualAddress
rtrPatVirtualAddress.description: The virtual IP Address used for translation

rtrPatLowestPort.name: rtrPatLowestPort
rtrPatLowestPort.description: Lowest Port number for this PAT entry

rtrPatHighestPort.name: rtrPatHighestPort
rtrPatHighestPort.description: Highest Port number for this PAT entry

rtrPatProtocol.name: rtrPatProtocol
rtrPatProtocol.description: Protocol selected. This Protocol and port range (lowest port - highest port) define the application (FTP, Telnet, SMTP etc.). Protocol enumaration numbers correspond to IP header 'protocol' field

rtrPatStatus.name: rtrPatStatus
rtrPatStatus.description: This object enables creating and deleting entries of the table.

rtrFACSDefaultAction.name: rtrFACSDefaultAction
rtrFACSDefaultAction.description: Used to define the default action for the device, when no FACS statements applicable to a given frame are defined.

rtrFACSActEntry.name: rtrFACSActEntry
rtrFACSActEntry.description: Each rtrFACSActEntry consist of the following parameters

rtrFACSActType.name: rtrFACSActType
rtrFACSActType.description: This parameter indicates on which FACS Table the FACS action will preform.

rtrFACSActIfIndex.name: rtrFACSActIfIndex
rtrFACSActIfIndex.description: The interface to which this FACS entry is applicable.

rtrFACSAction.name: rtrFACSAction
rtrFACSAction.description: The management station that sends a SET request for one of these actions with indexes rtrFACSType and rtrFACSIfIndex defines the type and the interface Id for which all FACS statements are to be erased. If no interface or no type is specified, all FACS statements for a protocol are erased.

rtrFACSActiveDB.name: rtrFACSActiveDB
rtrFACSActiveDB.description: This parameter will point on which Facs DataBase the SNMP agent read. The Active dataBase is Read Only. The user may change FACS statements in the temporary DataBase and then write it to the Active DB.

rtrFACSEntry.name: rtrFACSEntry
rtrFACSEntry.description: Each FACS statment consists of the following parameters

rtrFACSIfIndex.name: rtrFACSIfIndex
rtrFACSIfIndex.description: The interface to which this FACS entry is applicable. For applications this variables is always 0.

rtrFACSProtocolType.name: rtrFACSProtocolType
rtrFACSProtocolType.description: This parameter define the protocol the Security Access Control is applicable.

rtrFACSType.name: rtrFACSType
rtrFACSType.description: The Mode of in which this FACS statement operates. For applications this variable is always rx(2).

rtrFACSSrcAdd.name: rtrFACSSrcAdd
rtrFACSSrcAdd.description: The size of the octet string will be according to the protocol type defined in rtrFACSProtocolType.

rtrFACSDesAdd.name: rtrFACSDesAdd
rtrFACSDesAdd.description: Destination-address The size of the octet string will be according to the protocol type define in rtrFACSProtocolType .

rtrFACSSocketNum.name: rtrFACSSocketNum
rtrFACSSocketNum.description: Port/socket number for different applications 0 is default meaning not applicable. none(1), ftp(21), telnet(23), smtp(25), tftp(69), snmp(161), snmpTrap(162), rip(520), sapIPX(1106), ripIPX(1107)

rtrFACSMask1Id.name: rtrFACSMask1Id
rtrFACSMask1Id.description: Index into RND mask table FACS/COD Type) .

rtrFACSMask2Id.name: rtrFACSMask2Id
rtrFACSMask2Id.description: Index into RND mask table FACS/COD according to the value of rtrFACSType .

rtrFACSStatus.name: rtrFACSStatus
rtrFACSStatus.description: The status of a table entry.

rtrFACSFrameData.name: rtrFACSFrameData
rtrFACSFrameData.description: Data from the frame that violated a FACS Filter.

rtrBridgePortConfigEntry.name: rtrBridgePortConfigEntry
rtrBridgePortConfigEntry.description: Each entry defines a bridge port

rtrBridgePortCIndex.name: rtrBridgePortCIndex
rtrBridgePortCIndex.description: This is the index of the bridge port. It is the same as 'dot1dBasePort' of the Bridge MIB.

rtrBridgePortCIf.name: rtrBridgePortCIf
rtrBridgePortCIf.description: The config ifIndex the bridge port is sitting on.

rtrBridgePortCStatus.name: rtrBridgePortCStatus
rtrBridgePortCStatus.description: The status of the RtrBridgePortConfigEntry. Creating and destroying the bridge port is done by this variable.

rtrConfigEntry.name: rtrConfigEntry
rtrConfigEntry.description: An entry in the Router's Configuration table.

rtrConfigIndex.name: rtrConfigIndex
rtrConfigIndex.description: This object indicates the Router's Index.

rtrConfigClassifierTosMask.name: rtrConfigClassifierTosMask
rtrConfigClassifierTosMask.description: This object indicates the Classifier's TOS Mask, as follows: 0x1C for DTR -- rfc795 0x1E for Cisco 0xE0 for Precedence -- rfc795 0xFC for Diffserv Else for Manual .

rtrConfigRIPMode.name: rtrConfigRIPMode
rtrConfigRIPMode.description: This object determines the Router Information Protocol to measure the shortest path between 2 positions on the network.

rtrFwdEntry.name: rtrFwdEntry
rtrFwdEntry.description: An entry in the Router's Forwarding table.

rtrFwdIdx.name: rtrFwdIdx
rtrFwdIdx.description: This object indicates the Router Index.

rtrFwdIpAddress.name: rtrFwdIpAddress
rtrFwdIpAddress.description: This object indicates the Destination IP Address.

rtrFwdIpMask.name: rtrFwdIpMask
rtrFwdIpMask.description: This object indicates the Mask IP address.

rtrFwdRuleIdx.name: rtrFwdRuleIdx
rtrFwdRuleIdx.description: This object indicates the Rule's Number.

rtrFwdRowStatus.name: rtrFwdRowStatus
rtrFwdRowStatus.description: This object enables the user to create/delete entries in this table. Entry of Type rtrFwdType = staticRouting(3) are created by the user. Only this type of entries can be deleted by the user. Entry of Type rtrFwdType = interface(2) are created/deleted automatically by the Agent when the user creates/deletes an interface of the Router.

rtrFwdNextHop.name: rtrFwdNextHop
rtrFwdNextHop.description: This object indicates the IP Address of the Next Hop.

rtrFwdIfIndex.name: rtrFwdIfIndex
rtrFwdIfIndex.description: This object indicates the Interface Index.

rtrFwdType.name: rtrFwdType
rtrFwdType.description: The type of route. Note that local(3) refers to a route for which the next hop is the final destination; remote(4) refers to a route for which the next hop is not the final destina- tion. Routes which do not result in traffic forwarding or rejection should not be displayed even if the implementation keeps them stored internally. reject (2) refers to a route which, if matched, discards the message as unreachable. This is used in some protocols as a means of correctly aggregating routes.

rtrFwdProto.name: rtrFwdProto
rtrFwdProto.description: The routing mechanism via which this route was learned. Inclusion of values for gateway routing protocols is not intended to imply that hosts should support those protocols.

rtrFwdEthQueue.name: rtrFwdEthQueue
rtrFwdEthQueue.description: This object indicates the ETH Queue number.

rtrFwdMetric1.name: rtrFwdMetric1
rtrFwdMetric1.description: The primary routing metric for this route. The semantics of this metric are determined by the routing-protocol specified in the route's rtrFwdProto value. If this metric is not used, its value should be set to -1.

rtrFACSViolation.name: rtrFACSViolation
rtrFACSViolation.description: The trap is sent for every violation of a FACS filter.

rtrSwDwnLoadTrap.name: rtrSwDwnLoadTrap
rtrSwDwnLoadTrap.description: The trap is sent after the tftp download of the software and before the decompression and reset operations.
